Sketch 1: Bounding Box

This sketch defines the outer limits of the violin silhouette and creates the inner boundary via Offset.

1. Geometry

Center-Point Rectangle:

Created using addCenterPointRectangle anchored to the origin.

Dimensions: width x height. (pulled from widthIn and heightIn in parameters)

Line IDs:

rect_T: Top edge

rect_R: Right edge

rect_B: Bottom edge

rect_L: Left edge

Diagonals:

Two construction lines used to define the center point.

Center Point (main_bounding_rectangle:C): The geometric center of the rectangle.

2. Constraints

Horizontal: rect_T, rect_B

Vertical: rect_L, rect_R

3. Steps

Offset:

Creates the inner boundary by offsetting the rectangle inward by the offset_distance.

This offset line becomes the reference for the four corners of the violin silhouette.   